parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Passenger Airbag Seat Occupancy Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag seat occupancy sensor can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death to the passenger.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard remains on
the passenger airbag light blinks or remains on
the airbag does not deploy in an accident
the passenger airbag is not activated when an adult passenger is in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death to the occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard remains on
the airbag does not deploy in an accident
the passenger airbag is not activated when an adult passenger is in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of ignition coils can cause the engine to misfire, leading to loss of power, hesitation, and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the valve cover O-ring can cause oil to leak into the spark plug cylinder holes, potentially leading to engine fires.
symptoms: Oil leakage into spark plug cylinder holes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to hesitate or stall, leading to loss of power and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the door locking system can cause doors to lock and not unlock, potentially trapping occupants inside the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: need to crawl over seats to exit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw of the inside door handles can cause razor-sharp edges, leading to cuts and injuries when opening doors.
symptoms: Cracked chrome paint on door handles
cuts and injuries when opening doors.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Coil and Spark Plug Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coils and spark plugs can cause the engine to shake violently, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: difficulty stopping or controlling the vehicle.
